#. lang="pi"><section class="sutta" id="dn31"><article><div class="hgroup"><p
#. class="division">
msgctxt "dn31:1.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 31"
msgstr "Long Discourses 31"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn31:2.1"
msgid "Siṅgālasutta"
msgstr "Advice to Sigālaka"

#. </h1></div><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.180"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:3.1"
msgid "<span class=\"evam\">Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​</span>"
msgstr "<span class=”evam”>So I have heard.</span>"

msgctxt "dn31:3.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

#. VAR: siṅgālako → sigālako (bj)
#. VAR: puthudisā → puthuddisā (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn31:3.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena siṅgālako gahapatiputto kālasseva uṭṭhāya rājagahā "
"nikkhamitvā allavattho allakeso pañjaliko puthudisā namassati—"
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the householder’s son Sigālaka rose early and left "
"Rājagaha. With his clothes and hair all wet, he raised his cupped hands to "
"revere the quarters—"

msgctxt "dn31:3.4"
msgid ""
"puratthimaṃ disaṃ dakkhiṇaṃ disaṃ pacchimaṃ disaṃ uttaraṃ disaṃ heṭṭhimaṃ "
"disaṃ uparimaṃ disaṃ."
msgstr "east, south, west, north, below, and above."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.181"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya rājagahaṃ "
"piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha got dressed in the morning and, taking his bowl and robes, "
"entered Rājagaha for alms."

msgctxt "dn31:4.2"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho bhagavā siṅgālakaṃ gahapatiputtaṃ kālasseva vuṭṭhāya rājagahā "
"nikkhamitvā allavatthaṃ allakesaṃ pañjalikaṃ puthudisā namassantaṃ—"
msgstr "He saw Sigālaka revering the quarters"

msgctxt "dn31:4.3"
msgid ""
"puratthimaṃ disaṃ dakkhiṇaṃ disaṃ pacchimaṃ disaṃ uttaraṃ disaṃ heṭṭhimaṃ "
"disaṃ uparimaṃ disaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn31:4.4"
msgid "Disvā siṅgālakaṃ gahapatiputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

msgctxt "dn31:4.5"
msgid ""
"“kiṃ nu kho tvaṃ, gahapatiputta, kālasseva vuṭṭhāya rājagahā nikkhamitvā "
"allavattho allakeso pañjaliko puthudisā namassasi—"
msgstr "“Householder’s son, why are you revering the quarters in this way?”"

msgctxt "dn31:4.6"
msgid ""
"puratthimaṃ disaṃ dakkhiṇaṃ disaṃ pacchimaṃ disaṃ uttaraṃ disaṃ heṭṭhimaṃ "
"disaṃ uparimaṃ disan”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn31:4.7"
msgid "“Pitā maṃ, bhante, kālaṃ karonto evaṃ avaca:"
msgstr "“Sir, on his deathbed my father said to me:"

msgctxt "dn31:4.8"
msgid "‘disā, tāta, namasseyyāsī’ti."
msgstr "‘My dear, please revere the quarters.’"

msgctxt "dn31:4.9"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, bhante, pituvacanaṃ sakkaronto garuṃ karonto mānento pūjento "
"kālasseva uṭṭhāya rājagahā nikkhamitvā allavattho allakeso pañjaliko "
"puthudisā namassāmi—"
msgstr ""
"Honoring, respecting, and venerating my father’s words, I rose early and "
"left Rājagaha and, with my clothes and hair all wet, raised my cupped hands "
"to revere the quarters—"

msgctxt "dn31:4.10"
msgid ""
"puratthimaṃ disaṃ dakkhiṇaṃ disaṃ pacchimaṃ disaṃ uttaraṃ disaṃ heṭṭhimaṃ "
"disaṃ uparimaṃ disan”ti."
msgstr "east, south, west, north, below, and above.”"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn31:5.1"
msgid "1. Cha disā"
msgstr "The Six Quarters"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a>
#. VAR: cha disā → chaddisā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn31:6.1"
msgid "“Na kho, gahapatiputta, ariyassa vinaye evaṃ cha disā namassitabbā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Householder’s son, that’s not how the six quarters should be revered in the "
"training of the noble one.”"

msgctxt "dn31:6.2"
msgid "“Yathā kathaṃ pana, bhante, ariyassa vinaye cha disā namassitabbā?"
msgstr ""
"“But sir, how should the six quarters be revered in the training of the "
"noble one?”"

msgctxt "dn31:6.3"
msgid ""
"Sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā tathā dhammaṃ desetu, yathā ariyassa vinaye cha "
"disā namassitabbā”ti."
msgstr "Sir, please teach me this.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:7.1"
msgid "“Tena hi, gahapatiputta, suṇohi sādhukaṃ manasikarohi bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, householder’s son, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "dn31:7.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho siṅgālako gahapatiputto bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Sigālaka."

msgctxt "dn31:7.3"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a>
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn31:8.1"
msgid ""
"“Yato kho, gahapatiputta, ariyasāvakassa cattāro kammakilesā pahīnā honti, "
"catūhi ca ṭhānehi pāpakammaṃ na karoti, cha ca bhogānaṃ apāyamukhāni na "
"sevati, so evaṃ cuddasa pāpakāpagato chaddisāpaṭicchādī ubholokavijayāya "
"paṭipanno hoti."
msgstr ""
"“Householder’s son, a noble disciple gives up four corrupt deeds, doesn’t do "
"bad deeds on four grounds, and avoids six drains on wealth. When they’ve "
"left these fourteen bad things behind they have the six quarters covered. "

msgctxt "dn31:8.2"
msgid "Tassa ayañceva loko āraddho hoti paro ca loko."
msgstr ""
"They’re practicing to win in both worlds, and they succeed in this world and "
"the next."

msgctxt "dn31:8.3"
msgid "So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a "
"heavenly realm."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn31:9.1"
msgid "2. Cattāro kammakilesā"
msgstr "Four Corrupt Deeds"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:10.1"
msgid "Katamassa cattāro kammakilesā pahīnā honti?"
msgstr "What four corrupt deeds have they given up?"

msgctxt "dn31:10.2"
msgid ""
"Pāṇātipāto kho, gahapatiputta, kammakileso, adinnādānaṃ kammakileso, "
"kāmesumicchācāro kammakileso, musāvādo kammakileso."
msgstr ""
"Killing living creatures, stealing, sexual misconduct, and lying: these are "
"corrupt deeds."

msgctxt "dn31:10.3"
msgid "Imassa cattāro kammakilesā pahīnā hontī”ti."
msgstr "These are the four corrupt deeds they’ve given up.”"

msgctxt "dn31:10.4"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "This is what the Buddha said."

#. VAR: Idaṃ vatvāna → idaṃ vatvā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn31:10.5"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.182"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:11.1"
msgid "“Pāṇātipāto adinnādānaṃ,"
msgstr "“Killing, stealing,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:11.2"
msgid "Musāvādo ca vuccati;"
msgstr "telling lies,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:11.3"
msgid "Paradāragamanañceva,"
msgstr "and committing adultery:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:11.4"
msgid "Nappasaṃsanti paṇḍitā”ti."
msgstr "astute people don’t praise these things.”"

#. </p></blockquote><h2>
msgctxt "dn31:12.1"
msgid "3. Catuṭhānaṃ"
msgstr "Four Grounds"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:13.1"
msgid "“Katamehi catūhi ṭhānehi pāpakammaṃ na karoti?"
msgstr "“On what four grounds do they not do bad deeds?"

msgctxt "dn31:13.2"
msgid ""
"Chandāgatiṃ gacchanto pāpakammaṃ karoti, dosāgatiṃ gacchanto pāpakammaṃ "
"karoti, mohāgatiṃ gacchanto pāpakammaṃ karoti, bhayāgatiṃ gacchanto "
"pāpakammaṃ karoti."
msgstr ""
"One does bad deeds prejudiced by favoritism, hostility, stupidity, and "
"cowardice."

msgctxt "dn31:13.3"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, gahapatiputta, ariyasāvako neva chandāgatiṃ gacchati, na dosāgatiṃ "
"gacchati, na mohāgatiṃ gacchati, na bhayāgatiṃ gacchati;"
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple is not prejudiced by favoritism, hostility, stupidity, "
"and cowardice,"

msgctxt "dn31:13.4"
msgid "imehi catūhi ṭhānehi pāpakammaṃ na karotī”ti."
msgstr "they don’t do bad deeds on these four grounds.”"

msgctxt "dn31:13.5"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "This is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "dn31:13.6"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:14.1"
msgid "“Chandā dosā bhayā mohā,"
msgstr "“If you act against the Dharma"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:14.2"
msgid "yo dhammaṃ ativattati;"
msgstr "out of favoritism, hostility, cowardice, or stupidity,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: tassa → tassa yaso (bahūsu)
msgctxt "dn31:14.3"
msgid "Nihīyati yaso tassa,"
msgstr "your fame shrinks,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:14.4"
msgid "kāḷapakkheva candimā."
msgstr "like the moon in the dark fortnight."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:15.1"
msgid "Chandā dosā bhayā mohā,"
msgstr "If you don’t act against the Dharma"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:15.2"
msgid "yo dhammaṃ nātivattati;"
msgstr "out of favoritism, hostility, cowardice, and stupidity,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: tassa → tassa yaso (bahūsu, vinayepi)
msgctxt "dn31:15.3"
msgid "Āpūrati yaso tassa,"
msgstr "your fame swells,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: sukkapakkheva → juṇhapakkheva (mr)
msgctxt "dn31:15.4"
msgid "sukkapakkheva candimā”ti."
msgstr "like the moon in the bright fortnight.”"

#. </p></blockquote><h2>
msgctxt "dn31:16.1"
msgid "4. Cha apāyamukhāni"
msgstr "Six Drains on Wealth"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:17.1"
msgid "“Katamāni cha bhogānaṃ apāyamukhāni na sevati?"
msgstr "“What six drains on wealth do they avoid?"

#. VAR: ālasyānuyogo → ālassānuyogo (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn31:17.2"
msgid ""
"Surāmerayamajjappamādaṭṭhānānuyogo kho, gahapatiputta, bhogānaṃ apāyamukhaṃ, "
"vikālavisikhācariyānuyogo bhogānaṃ apāyamukhaṃ, samajjābhicaraṇaṃ bhogānaṃ "
"apāyamukhaṃ, jūtappamādaṭṭhānānuyogo bhogānaṃ apāyamukhaṃ, pāpamittānuyogo "
"bhogānaṃ apāyamukhaṃ, ālasyānuyogo bhogānaṃ apāyamukhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Habitually engaging in the following things is a drain on wealth: drinking "
"alcohol; roaming the streets at night; frequenting festivals; gambling; bad "
"friends; laziness."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn31:18.1"
msgid "5. Surāmerayassa cha ādīnavā"
msgstr "Six Drawbacks of Drinking"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.183"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:19.1"
msgid "Cha khome, gahapatiputta, ādīnavā surāmerayamajjappamādaṭṭhānānuyoge."
msgstr "There are these six drawbacks of habitually drinking alcohol."

#. VAR: dhanajāni → dhanañjāni (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn31:19.2"
msgid ""
"Sandiṭṭhikā dhanajāni, kalahappavaḍḍhanī, rogānaṃ āyatanaṃ, akittisañjananī, "
"kopīnanidaṃsanī, paññāya dubbalikaraṇītveva chaṭṭhaṃ padaṃ bhavati."
msgstr ""
"Immediate loss of wealth, promotion of quarrels, susceptibility to illness, "
"disrepute, indecent exposure; and weakened wisdom is the sixth thing."

msgctxt "dn31:19.3"
msgid "Ime kho, gahapatiputta, cha ādīnavā surāmerayamajjappamādaṭṭhānānuyoge."
msgstr "These are the six drawbacks of habitually drinking alcohol."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn31:20.1"
msgid "6. Vikālacariyāya cha ādīnavā"
msgstr "Roaming the Streets at Night"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:21.1"
msgid "Cha khome, gahapatiputta, ādīnavā vikālavisikhācariyānuyoge."
msgstr "There are these six drawbacks of roaming the streets at night."

#. VAR: ca hoti pāpakesu ṭhānesu → tesu tesu ṭhānesu (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn31:21.2"
msgid ""
"Attāpissa agutto arakkhito hoti, puttadāropissa agutto arakkhito hoti, "
"sāpateyyampissa aguttaṃ arakkhitaṃ hoti, saṅkiyo ca hoti pāpakesu ṭhānesu, "
"abhūtavacanañca tasmiṃ rūhati, bahūnañca dukkhadhammānaṃ purakkhato hoti."
msgstr ""
"Yourself, your partner and children, and your property are all left "
"unguarded. You’re suspected of bad deeds. Untrue rumors spread about you. "
"You’re at the forefront of many things that entail suffering."

msgctxt "dn31:21.3"
msgid "Ime kho, gahapatiputta, cha ādīnavā vikālavisikhācariyānuyoge."
msgstr "These are the six drawbacks of roaming the streets at night."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn31:22.1"
msgid "7. Samajjābhicaraṇassa cha ādīnavā"
msgstr "Six Drawbacks of Festivals"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:23.1"
msgid "Cha khome, gahapatiputta, ādīnavā samajjābhicaraṇe."
msgstr "There are these six drawbacks of frequenting festivals."

#. VAR: Kva → kuvaṃ (si, pts1)
msgctxt "dn31:23.2"
msgid ""
"Kva naccaṃ, kva gītaṃ, kva vāditaṃ, kva akkhānaṃ, kva pāṇissaraṃ, kva "
"kumbhathunanti."
msgstr ""
"You’re always thinking: ‘Where’s the dancing? Where’s the singing? Where’s "
"the music? Where are the stories? Where’s the applause? Where are the kettle-"
"drums?’"

msgctxt "dn31:23.3"
msgid "Ime kho, gahapatiputta, cha ādīnavā samajjābhicaraṇe."
msgstr "These are the six drawbacks of frequenting festivals."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn31:24.1"
msgid "8. Jūtappamādassa cha ādīnavā"
msgstr "Six Drawbacks of Gambling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:25.1"
msgid "Cha khome, gahapatiputta, ādīnavā jūtappamādaṭṭhānānuyoge."
msgstr "There are these six drawbacks of habitually gambling."

#. VAR: sabhāgatassa → sabhāye tassa (mr)
msgctxt "dn31:25.2"
msgid ""
"Jayaṃ veraṃ pasavati, jino vittamanusocati, sandiṭṭhikā dhanajāni, "
"sabhāgatassa vacanaṃ na rūhati, mittāmaccānaṃ paribhūto hoti, "
"āvāhavivāhakānaṃ apatthito hoti:"
msgstr ""
"Victory breeds enmity. The loser mourns their money. There is immediate loss "
"of wealth. A gambler’s word carries no weight in public assembly. Friends "
"and colleagues treat them with contempt. And no-one wants to marry a "
"gambler, for they think:"

msgctxt "dn31:25.3"
msgid "‘akkhadhutto ayaṃ purisapuggalo nālaṃ dārabharaṇāyā’ti."
msgstr "‘This individual is a gambler—they’re not able to support a partner.’"

msgctxt "dn31:25.4"
msgid "Ime kho, gahapatiputta, cha ādīnavā jūtappamādaṭṭhānānuyoge."
msgstr "These are the six drawbacks of habitually gambling."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn31:26.1"
msgid "9. Pāpamittatāya cha ādīnavā"
msgstr "Six Drawbacks of Bad Friends"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.184"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:27.1"
msgid "Cha khome, gahapatiputta, ādīnavā pāpamittānuyoge."
msgstr "There are these six drawbacks of bad friends."

msgctxt "dn31:27.2"
msgid "Ye dhuttā, ye soṇḍā, ye pipāsā, ye nekatikā, ye vañcanikā, ye sāhasikā."
msgstr ""
"You become friends and companions with those who are scoundrels, drunkards, "
"addicts, frauds, swindlers, and thugs."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn31:27.3"
msgid "Tyāssa mittā honti te sahāyā."
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn31:27.4"
msgid "Ime kho, gahapatiputta, cha ādīnavā pāpamittānuyoge."
msgstr "These are the six drawbacks of bad friends."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn31:28.1"
msgid "10. Ālasyassa cha ādīnavā"
msgstr "Six Drawbacks of Laziness"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:29.1"
msgid "Cha khome, gahapatiputta, ādīnavā ālasyānuyoge."
msgstr "There are these six drawbacks of habitual laziness."

msgctxt "dn31:29.2"
msgid ""
"Atisītanti kammaṃ na karoti, atiuṇhanti kammaṃ na karoti, atisāyanti kammaṃ "
"na karoti, atipātoti kammaṃ na karoti, atichātosmīti kammaṃ na karoti, "
"atidhātosmīti kammaṃ na karoti."
msgstr ""
"You don’t get your work done because you think: ‘It’s too cold! It’s too "
"hot. It’s too late! It’s too early! I’m too hungry! I’m too full!’"

msgctxt "dn31:29.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa evaṃ kiccāpadesabahulassa viharato anuppannā ceva bhogā nuppajjanti, "
"uppannā ca bhogā parikkhayaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr ""
"By dwelling on so many excuses for not working, you don’t make any more "
"money, and the money you already have runs out."

msgctxt "dn31:29.4"
msgid "Ime kho, gahapatiputta, cha ādīnavā ālasyānuyoge”ti."
msgstr "These are the six drawbacks of habitual laziness.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:30.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "This is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "dn31:30.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:31.1"
msgid "“Hoti pānasakhā nāma,"
msgstr "“Some are just drinking buddies,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:31.2"
msgid "hoti sammiyasammiyo;"
msgstr "some call you their dear, dear friend,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:31.3"
msgid "Yo ca atthesu jātesu,"
msgstr "but a true friend is one"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:31.4"
msgid "sahāyo hoti so sakhā."
msgstr "who stands by you in need."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:32.1"
msgid "Ussūraseyyā paradārasevanā,"
msgstr "Sleeping late, adultery,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Verappasavo → verappasaṅgo (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn31:32.2"
msgid "Verappasavo ca anatthatā ca;"
msgstr "making enemies, harmfulness,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:32.3"
msgid "Pāpā ca mittā sukadariyatā ca,"
msgstr "bad friends, and avarice:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:32.4"
msgid "Ete cha ṭhānā purisaṃ dhaṃsayanti."
msgstr "these six grounds ruin a person."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:33.1"
msgid "Pāpamitto pāpasakho,"
msgstr "With bad friends, bad companions,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:33.2"
msgid "pāpaācāragocaro;"
msgstr "bad conduct, hanging out in bad places,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:33.3"
msgid "Asmā lokā paramhā ca,"
msgstr "a man falls to ruin"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:33.4"
msgid "ubhayā dhaṃsate naro."
msgstr "in both this world and the next."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:34.1"
msgid "Akkhitthiyo vāruṇī naccagītaṃ,"
msgstr "Dice, women, drink, song and dance;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:34.2"
msgid "Divā soppaṃ pāricariyā akāle;"
msgstr "sleeping by day and roaming at night;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:34.3"
msgid "Pāpā ca mittā sukadariyatā ca,"
msgstr "bad friends, and avarice:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:34.4"
msgid "Ete cha ṭhānā purisaṃ dhaṃsayanti."
msgstr "these six grounds ruin a person."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.185"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:35.1"
msgid "Akkhehi dibbanti suraṃ pivanti,"
msgstr "They play dice and drink liquor,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:35.2"
msgid "Yantitthiyo pāṇasamā paresaṃ;"
msgstr "and consort with women loved by others."

#. <br>
#. VAR: vuddhasevī → vuddhisevī (s1-3) | buddhisevī (mr)
msgctxt "dn31:35.3"
msgid "Nihīnasevī na ca vuddhasevī,"
msgstr "Associating with the worse, not the better,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:35.4"
msgid "Nihīyate kāḷapakkheva cando."
msgstr "they diminish like the waning moon."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:36.1"
msgid "Yo vāruṇī addhano akiñcano,"
msgstr "A drunkard, broke, and destitute,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Pipāso pivaṃ papāgato → pipāsosi atthapāgato (s1-3) | pipāso pibam
#. papāgato (pts1) | pipāsopi samappapāgato (mr)
msgctxt "dn31:36.2"
msgid "Pipāso pivaṃ papāgato;"
msgstr "thirsty, drinks in the bar."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:36.3"
msgid "Udakamiva iṇaṃ vigāhati,"
msgstr "Drowning in debt, "

# kāhiti is 3 sg fut for karoti.
#. <br>
#. VAR: Akulaṃ → ākulaṃ (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "dn31:36.4"
msgid "Akulaṃ kāhiti khippamattano."
msgstr "they’ll quickly lose their way."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:37.1"
msgid "Na divā soppasīlena,"
msgstr "When you’re in the habit of sleeping late,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:37.2"
msgid "rattimuṭṭhānadessinā;"
msgstr "seeing night as time to rise,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:37.3"
msgid "Niccaṃ mattena soṇḍena,"
msgstr "and always getting drunk,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:37.4"
msgid "sakkā āvasituṃ gharaṃ."
msgstr "you can’t keep up the household life."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:38.1"
msgid "Atisītaṃ atiuṇhaṃ,"
msgstr "‘Too cold, too hot,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:38.2"
msgid "atisāyamidaṃ ahu;"
msgstr "Too late,’ they say."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:38.3"
msgid "Iti vissaṭṭhakammante,"
msgstr "Neglecting their work like this,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:38.4"
msgid "atthā accenti māṇave."
msgstr "the young miss their chance."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:39.1"
msgid "Yodha sītañca uṇhañca,"
msgstr "But one who considers hot and cold"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:39.2"
msgid "tiṇā bhiyyo na maññati;"
msgstr "as nothing more than blades of grass—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:39.3"
msgid "Karaṃ purisakiccāni,"
msgstr "he does his manly duty,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: sukhaṃ → sukhā (sabbattha)
msgctxt "dn31:39.4"
msgid "so sukhaṃ na vihāyatī”ti."
msgstr "and happiness never fails.”"

#. </p></blockquote><h2>
msgctxt "dn31:40.1"
msgid "11. Mittapatirūpaka"
msgstr "Fake Friends"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:41.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, gahapatiputta, amittā mittapatirūpakā veditabbā."
msgstr ""
"“Householder’s son, you should recognize these four enemies disguised as "
"friends:"

msgctxt "dn31:41.2"
msgid ""
"Aññadatthuharo amitto mittapatirūpako veditabbo, vacīparamo amitto "
"mittapatirūpako veditabbo, anuppiyabhāṇī amitto mittapatirūpako veditabbo, "
"apāyasahāyo amitto mittapatirūpako veditabbo."
msgstr "the taker, the talker, the flatterer, the spender."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.186"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:42.1"
msgid ""
"Catūhi kho, gahapatiputta, ṭhānehi aññadatthuharo amitto mittapatirūpako "
"veditabbo."
msgstr "You can recognize a fake friend who’s all take on four grounds."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:43.1"
msgid "Aññadatthuharo hoti,"
msgstr "Your possessions end up theirs."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:43.2"
msgid "appena bahumicchati;"
msgstr "Giving little, they expect a lot."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:43.3"
msgid "Bhayassa kiccaṃ karoti,"
msgstr "They do their duty out of fear."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:43.4"
msgid "sevati atthakāraṇā."
msgstr "They associate for their own advantage."

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:44.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, catūhi ṭhānehi aññadatthuharo amitto "
"mittapatirūpako veditabbo."
msgstr "You can recognize a fake friend who’s all take on these four grounds."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:45.1"
msgid ""
"Catūhi kho, gahapatiputta, ṭhānehi vacīparamo amitto mittapatirūpako "
"veditabbo."
msgstr "You can recognize a fake friend who’s all talk on four grounds."

#. VAR: paṭisantharati → paṭisandharati (mr)
msgctxt "dn31:45.2"
msgid ""
"Atītena paṭisantharati, anāgatena paṭisantharati, niratthakena saṅgaṇhāti, "
"paccuppannesu kiccesu byasanaṃ dasseti."
msgstr ""
"They’re hospitable in the past. They’re hospitable in the future. They’re "
"full of meaningless pleasantries. When something needs doing in the present "
"they point to their own misfortune."

msgctxt "dn31:45.3"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, catūhi ṭhānehi vacīparamo amitto mittapatirūpako "
"veditabbo."
msgstr "You can recognize a fake friend who’s all talk on these four grounds."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:46.1"
msgid ""
"Catūhi kho, gahapatiputta, ṭhānehi anuppiyabhāṇī amitto mittapatirūpako "
"veditabbo."
msgstr "You can recognize a fake friend who’s a flatterer on four grounds."

#. VAR: Pāpakampissa → pāpakam­maṃ­pissa (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn31:46.2"
msgid ""
"Pāpakampissa anujānāti, kalyāṇampissa anujānāti, sammukhāssa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, "
"parammukhāssa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati."
msgstr ""
"They support you equally in doing bad and doing good. They praise you to you "
"face, and put you down behind your back."

msgctxt "dn31:46.3"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, catūhi ṭhānehi anuppiyabhāṇī amitto "
"mittapatirūpako veditabbo."
msgstr ""
"You can recognize a fake friend who’s a flatterer on these four grounds."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:47.1"
msgid ""
"Catūhi kho, gahapatiputta, ṭhānehi apāyasahāyo amitto mittapatirūpako "
"veditabbo."
msgstr "You can recognize a fake friend who’s a spender on four grounds."

msgctxt "dn31:47.2"
msgid ""
"Surāmerayamajjappamādaṭṭhānānuyoge sahāyo hoti, vikālavisikhācariyānuyoge "
"sahāyo hoti, samajjābhicaraṇe sahāyo hoti, jūtappamādaṭṭhānānuyoge sahāyo "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"They accompany you when drinking, roaming the streets at night, frequenting "
"festivals, and gambling."

msgctxt "dn31:47.3"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, catūhi ṭhānehi apāyasahāyo amitto mittapatirūpako "
"veditabbo”ti."
msgstr "You can recognize a fake friend who’s a spender on these four grounds.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:48.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "This is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "dn31:48.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:49.1"
msgid "“Aññadatthuharo mitto,"
msgstr "“One friend is all take,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: vacīparo → vacīparamo (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn31:49.2"
msgid "yo ca mitto vacīparo;"
msgstr "another all talk;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:49.3"
msgid "Anuppiyañca yo āha,"
msgstr "one’s just a flatterer,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:49.4"
msgid "apāyesu ca yo sakhā."
msgstr "and one a friend who spends."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:50.1"
msgid "Ete amitte cattāro,"
msgstr "An astute person understands"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:50.2"
msgid "iti viññāya paṇḍito;"
msgstr "these four enemies for what they are"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:50.3"
msgid "Ārakā parivajjeyya,"
msgstr "and keeps them at a distance,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:50.4"
msgid "maggaṃ paṭibhayaṃ yathā”ti."
msgstr "as they’d shun a risky road.”"

#. </p></blockquote><h2>
msgctxt "dn31:51.1"
msgid "12. Suhadamitta"
msgstr "Good-Hearted Friends"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="38"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.187"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:52.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, gahapatiputta, mittā suhadā veditabbā."
msgstr ""
"“Householder’s son, you should recognize these four good-hearted friends:"

#. VAR: Upakāro → upakārako (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn31:52.2"
msgid ""
"Upakāro mitto suhado veditabbo, samānasukhadukkho mitto suhado veditabbo, "
"atthakkhāyī mitto suhado veditabbo, anukampako mitto suhado veditabbo."
msgstr ""
"the helper, the friend in good times and bad, the counselor, and the one who’"
"s compassionate."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="39"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:53.1"
msgid "Catūhi kho, gahapatiputta, ṭhānehi upakāro mitto suhado veditabbo."
msgstr "You can recognize a good-hearted friend who’s a helper on four grounds."

msgctxt "dn31:53.2"
msgid ""
"Pamattaṃ rakkhati, pamattassa sāpateyyaṃ rakkhati, bhītassa saraṇaṃ hoti, "
"uppannesu kiccakaraṇīyesu taddiguṇaṃ bhogaṃ anuppadeti."
msgstr ""
"They guard you when you’re negligent. They guard your property when you’re "
"negligent. They keep you safe in times of danger. When something needs "
"doing, they supply you with twice the money you need."

msgctxt "dn31:53.3"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, catūhi ṭhānehi upakāro mitto suhado veditabbo."
msgstr ""
"You can recognize a good-hearted friend who’s a helper on these four grounds."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="40"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:54.1"
msgid ""
"Catūhi kho, gahapatiputta, ṭhānehi samānasukhadukkho mitto suhado veditabbo."
msgstr ""
"You can recognize a good-hearted friend who’s the same in good times and bad "
"on four grounds."

msgctxt "dn31:54.2"
msgid ""
"Guyhamassa ācikkhati, guyhamassa parigūhati, āpadāsu na vijahati, "
"jīvitaṃpissa atthāya pariccattaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"They tell you secrets. They keep your secrets. They don’t abandon you in "
"times of trouble. They’d even give their life for you."

msgctxt "dn31:54.3"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, catūhi ṭhānehi samānasukhadukkho mitto suhado "
"veditabbo."
msgstr ""
"You can recognize a good-hearted friend who’s the same in good times and bad "
"on these four grounds."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="41"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:55.1"
msgid "Catūhi kho, gahapatiputta, ṭhānehi atthakkhāyī mitto suhado veditabbo."
msgstr ""
"You can recognize a good-hearted friend who’s a counselor on four grounds."

msgctxt "dn31:55.2"
msgid ""
"Pāpā nivāreti, kalyāṇe niveseti, assutaṃ sāveti, saggassa maggaṃ ācikkhati."
msgstr ""
"They keep you from doing bad. They support you in doing good. They teach you "
"what you do not know. They explain the path to heaven."

msgctxt "dn31:55.3"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, catūhi ṭhānehi atthakkhāyī mitto suhado veditabbo."
msgstr ""
"You can recognize a good-hearted friend who’s a counselor on these four "
"grounds."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="42"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:56.1"
msgid "Catūhi kho, gahapatiputta, ṭhānehi anukampako mitto suhado veditabbo."
msgstr ""
"You can recognize a good-hearted friend who’s compassionate on four grounds."

msgctxt "dn31:56.2"
msgid ""
"Abhavenassa na nandati, bhavenassa nandati, avaṇṇaṃ bhaṇamānaṃ nivāreti, "
"vaṇṇaṃ bhaṇamānaṃ pasaṃsati."
msgstr ""
"They don’t delight in your misfortune. They delight in your good fortune. "
"They keep others from criticizing you. They encourage praise of you."

msgctxt "dn31:56.3"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, catūhi ṭhānehi anukampako mitto suhado "
"veditabbo”ti."
msgstr ""
"You can recognize a good-hearted friend who’s compassionate on these four "
"grounds."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="43"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:57.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "This is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "dn31:57.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="44"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.188"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:58.1"
msgid "“Upakāro ca yo mitto,"
msgstr "“A friend who’s a helper,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: sukhe dukkhe → sukhadukkho (s1-3, mr)
#. VAR: ca yo sakhā → yo ca mitto sukhe dukhe (bj) | yo ca mitto sukhe dukkhe
#. (si, pts1)
msgctxt "dn31:58.2"
msgid "sukhe dukkhe ca yo sakhā;"
msgstr "one the same in both pleasure and pain,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:58.3"
msgid "Atthakkhāyī ca yo mitto,"
msgstr "a friend of good counsel,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:58.4"
msgid "yo ca mittānukampako."
msgstr "and one of compassion."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="45"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:59.1"
msgid "Etepi mitte cattāro,"
msgstr "An astute person understands"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:59.2"
msgid "iti viññāya paṇḍito;"
msgstr "these four friends for what they are"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:59.3"
msgid "Sakkaccaṃ payirupāseyya,"
msgstr "and carefully looks after them,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:59.4"
msgid "mātā puttaṃva orasaṃ;"
msgstr "like a mother the child at her breast."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:59.5"
msgid "Paṇḍito sīlasampanno,"
msgstr "The astute and virtuous"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:59.6"
msgid "jalaṃ aggīva bhāsati."
msgstr "shine like a burning flame."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="46"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:60.1"
msgid "Bhoge saṃharamānassa,"
msgstr "They pick up riches"

# Several translators have bees gathering honey, which must be a very different kind of bee! the point of the simile is that money just tends to stick to those of good conduct.
#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:60.2"
msgid "bhamarasseva irīyato;"
msgstr "like bees pollen as they move about."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:60.3"
msgid "Bhogā sannicayaṃ yanti,"
msgstr "And their riches proceed to grow,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:60.4"
msgid "vammikovupacīyati."
msgstr "like an ant-hill piling up."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="47"></a>
#. VAR: samāhatvā → samāharitvā (s1-3) | samāhantvā (pts1)
msgctxt "dn31:61.1"
msgid "Evaṃ bhoge samāhatvā,"
msgstr "In gathering wealth like this,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:61.2"
msgid "alamatto kule gihī;"
msgstr "a householder does enough for their family."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:61.3"
msgid "Catudhā vibhaje bhoge,"
msgstr "And they’d hold on to friends"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:61.4"
msgid "sa ve mittāni ganthati."
msgstr "by dividing their wealth in four."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="48"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:62.1"
msgid "Ekena bhoge bhuñjeyya,"
msgstr "One portion is to enjoy."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:62.2"
msgid "dvīhi kammaṃ payojaye;"
msgstr "Two parts invest in work."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:62.3"
msgid "Catutthañca nidhāpeyya,"
msgstr "And the fourth should be kept"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:62.4"
msgid "āpadāsu bhavissatī”ti."
msgstr "for times of trouble.”"

#. </p></blockquote><h2>
msgctxt "dn31:63.1"
msgid "13. Chaddisāpaṭicchādanakaṇḍa"
msgstr "Covering the Six Directions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="49"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.189"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:64.1"
msgid "“Kathañca, gahapatiputta, ariyasāvako chaddisāpaṭicchādī hoti?"
msgstr ""
"“And how, householder’s son, does a noble disciple cover the six quarters?"

msgctxt "dn31:64.2"
msgid "Cha imā, gahapatiputta, disā veditabbā."
msgstr "These six quarters should be recognized:"

msgctxt "dn31:64.3"
msgid ""
"Puratthimā disā mātāpitaro veditabbā, dakkhiṇā disā ācariyā veditabbā, "
"pacchimā disā puttadārā veditabbā, uttarā disā mittāmaccā veditabbā, "
"heṭṭhimā disā dāsakammakarā veditabbā, uparimā disā samaṇabrāhmaṇā veditabbā."
msgstr ""
"parents as the east, teachers as the south, partner and children as the "
"west, friends and colleagues as the north, bondservants and workers as "
"beneath, and ascetics and brahmins as above."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="50"></a>
#. VAR: ne → nesaṃ (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn31:65.1"
msgid ""
"Pañcahi kho, gahapatiputta, ṭhānehi puttena puratthimā disā mātāpitaro "
"paccupaṭṭhātabbā—"
msgstr ""
"A child should serve their parents as the eastern quarter in five ways. "

#. VAR: bharissāmi → sambharissāmi (bj)
msgctxt "dn31:65.2"
msgid ""
"bhato ne bharissāmi, kiccaṃ nesaṃ karissāmi, kulavaṃsaṃ ṭhapessāmi, dāyajjaṃ "
"paṭipajjāmi, atha vā pana petānaṃ kālaṅkatānaṃ dakkhiṇaṃ anuppadassāmīti."
msgstr ""
"Thinking: ‘I will support those who supported me. I’ll do my duty for them. "
"I’ll maintain the family traditions. I’ll take care of the inheritance. When "
"they have passed away, I’ll make an offering on their behalf.’"

msgctxt "dn31:65.3"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, pañcahi ṭhānehi puttena puratthimā disā mātāpitaro "
"paccupaṭṭhitā pañcahi ṭhānehi puttaṃ anukampanti."
msgstr ""
"Parents served by the children in these five ways show compassion to them in "
"five ways."

#. VAR: niyyādenti → niyyātenti (bj)
msgctxt "dn31:65.4"
msgid ""
"Pāpā nivārenti, kalyāṇe nivesenti, sippaṃ sikkhāpenti, patirūpena dārena "
"saṃyojenti, samaye dāyajjaṃ niyyādenti."
msgstr "they keep them from doing bad and encourage them in doing good, "

msgctxt "dn31:65.5"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, pañcahi ṭhānehi puttena puratthimā disā mātāpitaro "
"paccupaṭṭhitā imehi pañcahi ṭhānehi puttaṃ anukampanti."
msgstr ""
"Parents served by their children in these five ways show compassion to them "
"in these five ways."

msgctxt "dn31:65.6"
msgid "Evamassa esā puratthimā disā paṭicchannā hoti khemā appaṭibhayā."
msgstr ""
"And that’s how the western quarter is covered, kept safe and free of peril."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="51"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.190"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:66.1"
msgid ""
"Pañcahi kho, gahapatiputta, ṭhānehi antevāsinā dakkhiṇā disā ācariyā "
"paccupaṭṭhātabbā—"
msgstr ""
"A student should serve their teacher as the southern quarter in five ways:"

#. VAR: sussusāya → sussūsāya (pts1, c-a)
msgctxt "dn31:66.2"
msgid ""
"uṭṭhānena upaṭṭhānena sussusāya pāricariyāya sakkaccaṃ sippapaṭiggahaṇena."
msgstr ""
"by rising for them, by serving them, by listening well, by looking after "
"them, and by carefully learning their profession."

msgctxt "dn31:66.3"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, pañcahi ṭhānehi antevāsinā dakkhiṇā disā ācariyā "
"paccupaṭṭhitā pañcahi ṭhānehi antevāsiṃ anukampanti—"
msgstr ""
"Teachers served by their students in these five ways show compassion to them "
"in five ways."

# the last is a little obscure. I think it means that, when the student has completed their studies and goes off to travel, the teacher does what they can to ensure their protection in other regions.
#. VAR: paṭiyādenti → paṭivedenti (s1-3) | parivedenti (pts1)
msgctxt "dn31:66.4"
msgid ""
"suvinītaṃ vinenti, suggahitaṃ gāhāpenti, sabbasippassutaṃ samakkhāyino "
"bhavanti, mittāmaccesu paṭiyādenti, disāsu parittāṇaṃ karonti."
msgstr ""
"They make sure you’re well trained and well educated. They clearly explain "
"all the knowledge of the profession. They introduce you to their friends and "
"colleagues. They provide protection in every region."

msgctxt "dn31:66.5"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, pañcahi ṭhānehi antevāsinā dakkhiṇā disā ācariyā "
"paccupaṭṭhitā imehi pañcahi ṭhānehi antevāsiṃ anukampanti."
msgstr ""
"Teachers served by their students in these five ways show compassion to them "
"in these five ways."

msgctxt "dn31:66.6"
msgid "Evamassa esā dakkhiṇā disā paṭicchannā hoti khemā appaṭibhayā."
msgstr ""
"And that’s how the southern quarter is covered, kept safe and free of peril."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="52"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:67.1"
msgid ""
"Pañcahi kho, gahapatiputta, ṭhānehi sāmikena pacchimā disā bhariyā "
"paccupaṭṭhātabbā—"
msgstr "A husband should serve their wife as the western quarter in five ways:"

#. VAR: anavamānanāya → avimānanāya (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn31:67.2"
msgid ""
"sammānanāya anavamānanāya anaticariyāya issariyavossaggena "
"alaṅkārānuppadānena."
msgstr ""
"by treating her with honor, by not looking down on her, by not being "
"unfaithful, by relinquishing sovereignty to her, and by presenting her with "
"adornments."

msgctxt "dn31:67.3"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, pañcahi ṭhānehi sāmikena pacchimā disā bhariyā "
"paccupaṭṭhitā pañcahi ṭhānehi sāmikaṃ anukampati—"
msgstr ""
"A wife served by her husband in these five ways shows compassion to him in "
"five ways."

msgctxt "dn31:67.4"
msgid ""
"susaṃvihitakammantā ca hoti, saṅgahitaparijanā ca, anaticārinī ca, "
"sambhatañca anurakkhati, dakkhā ca hoti analasā sabbakiccesu."
msgstr ""
"She’s well-organized in her work. She manages the domestic help. She’s not "
"unfaithful. She protects his earnings. She’s expert and tireless in all her "
"duties."

msgctxt "dn31:67.5"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, pañcahi ṭhānehi sāmikena pacchimā disā bhariyā "
"paccupaṭṭhitā imehi pañcahi ṭhānehi sāmikaṃ anukampati."
msgstr ""
"A wife served by her husband in these five ways shows compassion to him in "
"these five ways."

msgctxt "dn31:67.6"
msgid "Evamassa esā pacchimā disā paṭicchannā hoti khemā appaṭibhayā."
msgstr ""
"And that’s how the western quarter is covered, kept safe and free of peril."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="53"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:68.1"
msgid ""
"Pañcahi kho, gahapatiputta, ṭhānehi kulaputtena uttarā disā mittāmaccā "
"paccupaṭṭhātabbā—"
msgstr ""
"A respectable person should serve their friends and colleagues as the "
"southern quarter in five ways:"

#. VAR: peyyavajjena → piyavajjena (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "dn31:68.2"
msgid "dānena peyyavajjena atthacariyāya samānattatāya avisaṃvādanatāya."
msgstr "giving, kind speech, taking care, equality, and not using tricky words."

msgctxt "dn31:68.3"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, pañcahi ṭhānehi kulaputtena uttarā disā mittāmaccā "
"paccupaṭṭhitā pañcahi ṭhānehi kulaputtaṃ anukampanti—"
msgstr ""
"Friends and colleagues served by a respectable person in these five ways "
"show compassion to them in five ways."

msgctxt "dn31:68.4"
msgid ""
"pamattaṃ rakkhanti, pamattassa sāpateyyaṃ rakkhanti, bhītassa saraṇaṃ honti, "
"āpadāsu na vijahanti, aparapajā cassa paṭipūjenti."
msgstr ""
"They guard you when you’re negligent. They guard your property when you’re "
"negligent. They keep you safe in times of danger. They don’t abandon you in "
"times of trouble. They honor your descendants."

msgctxt "dn31:68.5"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, pañcahi ṭhānehi kulaputtena uttarā disā mittāmaccā "
"paccupaṭṭhitā imehi pañcahi ṭhānehi kulaputtaṃ anukampanti."
msgstr ""
"Friends and colleagues served by a respectable person in these five ways "
"show compassion to them in these five ways."

msgctxt "dn31:68.6"
msgid "Evamassa esā uttarā disā paṭicchannā hoti khemā appaṭibhayā."
msgstr ""
"And that’s how the northern quarter is covered, kept safe and free of peril."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="54"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.191"></a>
#. VAR: ayyirakena → ayirakena (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn31:69.1"
msgid ""
"Pañcahi kho, gahapatiputta, ṭhānehi ayyirakena heṭṭhimā disā dāsakammakarā "
"paccupaṭṭhātabbā—"
msgstr ""
"A master should serve their bondservants and workers as the lower quarter in "
"five ways:"

msgctxt "dn31:69.2"
msgid ""
"yathābalaṃ kammantasaṃvidhānena bhattavetanānuppadānena gilānupaṭṭhānena "
"acchariyānaṃ rasānaṃ saṃvibhāgena samaye vossaggena."
msgstr ""
"by organizing work according to ability, by paying food and wages, by "
"nursing them when sick, by sharing special treats, and by giving time off "
"work."

msgctxt "dn31:69.3"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, pañcahi ṭhānehi ayyirakena heṭṭhimā disā "
"dāsakammakarā paccupaṭṭhitā pañcahi ṭhānehi ayyirakaṃ anukampanti—"
msgstr ""
"Bondservants and workers served by a master in these five ways show "
"compassion to them in five ways."

msgctxt "dn31:69.4"
msgid ""
"pubbuṭṭhāyino ca honti, pacchā nipātino ca, dinnādāyino ca, sukatakammakarā "
"ca, kittivaṇṇaharā ca."
msgstr ""
"They get up first, and go to bed last. They don’t steal. They do their work "
"well. And they promote a good reputation."

msgctxt "dn31:69.5"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, pañcahi ṭhānehi ayyirakena heṭṭhimā disā "
"dāsakammakarā paccupaṭṭhitā imehi pañcahi ṭhānehi ayyirakaṃ anukampanti."
msgstr ""
"Bondservants and workers served by a master in these five ways show "
"compassion to them in these five ways."

msgctxt "dn31:69.6"
msgid "Evamassa esā heṭṭhimā disā paṭicchannā hoti khemā appaṭibhayā."
msgstr ""
"And that’s how the lower quarter is covered, kept safe and free of peril."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="55"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:70.1"
msgid ""
"Pañcahi kho, gahapatiputta, ṭhānehi kulaputtena uparimā disā samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"paccupaṭṭhātabbā—"
msgstr ""
"A respectable person should serve ascetics and brahmins as the upper quarter "
"in five ways:"

msgctxt "dn31:70.2"
msgid ""
"mettena kāyakammena mettena vacīkammena mettena manokammena anāvaṭadvāratāya "
"āmisānuppadānena."
msgstr ""
"by loving deeds of body, speech, and mind, by not turning them away at the "
"gate, and by providing them with material needs."

msgctxt "dn31:70.3"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, pañcahi ṭhānehi kulaputtena uparimā disā "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇā paccupaṭṭhitā chahi ṭhānehi kulaputtaṃ anukampanti—"
msgstr ""
"Ascetics and brahmins served by a respectable person in these five ways show "
"compassion to them in five ways."

msgctxt "dn31:70.4"
msgid ""
"pāpā nivārenti, kalyāṇe nivesenti, kalyāṇena manasā anukampanti, assutaṃ "
"sāventi, sutaṃ pariyodāpenti, saggassa maggaṃ ācikkhanti."
msgstr ""
"They keep you from doing bad. They support you in doing good. They think of "
"you with kindly thoughts. They teach you what you do not know. They clarify "
"what you’ve already learned. They explain the path to heaven."

msgctxt "dn31:70.5"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, gahapatiputta, pañcahi ṭhānehi kulaputtena uparimā disā "
"samaṇabrāhmaṇā paccupaṭṭhitā imehi chahi ṭhānehi kulaputtaṃ anukampanti."
msgstr ""
"Ascetics and brahmins served by a respectable person in these five ways show "
"compassion to them in these five ways."

msgctxt "dn31:70.6"
msgid "Evamassa esā uparimā disā paṭicchannā hoti khemā appaṭibhayā”ti."
msgstr ""
"And that’s how the upper quarter is covered, kept safe and free of peril.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="56"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:71.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "This is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "dn31:71.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="57"></a><a class="pts"
#. id="pts3.192"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:72.1"
msgid "“Mātāpitā disā pubbā,"
msgstr "“Parents are the east,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:72.2"
msgid "ācariyā dakkhiṇā disā;"
msgstr "teachers the south,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:72.3"
msgid "Puttadārā disā pacchā,"
msgstr "wife and child the west,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:72.4"
msgid "mittāmaccā ca uttarā."
msgstr "friends the north,"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="58"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:73.1"
msgid "Dāsakammakarā heṭṭhā,"
msgstr "servants and workers below,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:73.2"
msgid "uddhaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇā;"
msgstr "and ascetics and brahmins above."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:73.3"
msgid "Etā disā namasseyya,"
msgstr "By honoring the quarters"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:73.4"
msgid "alamatto kule gihī."
msgstr "a householder does enough for their family."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="59"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:74.1"
msgid "Paṇḍito sīlasampanno,"
msgstr "The astute and the virtuous,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:74.2"
msgid "saṇho ca paṭibhānavā;"
msgstr "the gentle and the articulate,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:74.3"
msgid "Nivātavutti atthaddho,"
msgstr "the humble and the kind:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:74.4"
msgid "tādiso labhate yasaṃ."
msgstr "that’s who win glory."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="60"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:75.1"
msgid "Uṭṭhānako analaso,"
msgstr "The diligent, not lazy,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:75.2"
msgid "āpadāsu na vedhati;"
msgstr "those not disturbed by troubles,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:75.3"
msgid "Acchinnavutti medhāvī,"
msgstr "those consistent in conduct, the intelligent:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:75.4"
msgid "tādiso labhate yasaṃ."
msgstr "that’s who win glory."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="61"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:76.1"
msgid "Saṅgāhako mittakaro,"
msgstr "The inclusive, the makers of friends,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:76.2"
msgid "vadaññū vītamaccharo;"
msgstr "the kind, those rid of stinginess, "

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:76.3"
msgid "Netā vinetā anunetā,"
msgstr "those who lead, train, and persuade:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:76.4"
msgid "tādiso labhate yasaṃ."
msgstr "that’s who win glory."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="62"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:77.1"
msgid "Dānañca peyyavajjañca,"
msgstr "Giving and kindly words,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:77.2"
msgid "atthacariyā ca yā idha;"
msgstr "taking care here,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:77.3"
msgid "Samānattatā ca dhammesu,"
msgstr "and treating equally in worldly conditions,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:77.4"
msgid "tattha tattha yathārahaṃ;"
msgstr "as befits them in each case."

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:77.5"
msgid "Ete kho saṅgahā loke,"
msgstr "These ways of being inclusive in the world"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:77.6"
msgid "rathassāṇīva yāyato."
msgstr "are like a moving chariot’s linch-pin."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="63"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:78.1"
msgid "Ete ca saṅgahā nāssu,"
msgstr "If there were no such ways of being inclusive"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:78.2"
msgid "na mātā puttakāraṇā;"
msgstr "neither mother nor father"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:78.3"
msgid "Labhetha mānaṃ pūjaṃ vā,"
msgstr "would be respected and honored"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:78.4"
msgid "pitā vā puttakāraṇā."
msgstr "for what they’ve done for their children."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="64"></a><a class="pts" id="pts3.193"></a>
#. VAR: saṅgahā → saṅgahe (bj, pts1, c1)
msgctxt "dn31:79.1"
msgid "Yasmā ca saṅgahā ete,"
msgstr "But since these ways of being inclusive do exist,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: sammapekkhanti → samavekkhanti (bj, pts1, mr) | samapekkhanti (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn31:79.2"
msgid "sammapekkhanti paṇḍitā;"
msgstr "the astute do regard them well,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:79.3"
msgid "Tasmā mahattaṃ papponti,"
msgstr "so they achieve greatness"

#. <br>
msgctxt "dn31:79.4"
msgid "pāsaṃsā ca bhavanti te”ti."
msgstr "and are praised.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p><a class="sc" id="65"></a>
msgctxt "dn31:80.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, siṅgālako gahapatiputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When this was said, Sigālaka the householder’s son said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "dn31:80.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "“Excellent, sir! Excellent!"

msgctxt "dn31:80.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, "
"mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya ‘"
"cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti;"
msgstr ""
"Just as one might set upright what had been overturned, or reveal what had "
"been hidden, or show the way to one who was lost, or bring a lamp into the "
"darkness so that one with eyes might see what is there—"

msgctxt "dn31:80.4"
msgid "evamevaṃ bhagavatā anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr "so too the Buddha has made the teaching clear in many ways. "

msgctxt "dn31:80.5"
msgid ""
"Esāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the Dharma, and to the mendicant Saṅgha."

msgctxt "dn31:80.6"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhagavā dhāretu, ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may the Buddha remember me as a lay follower who has "
"gone for refuge for life.” "

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn31:81.1"
msgid "Siṅgālasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
